														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2861814">
									

<p>Gonna voice my opinion regarding the longer sub-designations, since this is a suitable platform to discuss this.</p>
<p>IMO, I feel that codenames for GOC TEs should not be too long. Perhaps two codenames or two codenames and a suffix (e.g. '-child') will suffice. When there are three or more are present (i.e. the sub-designations here), it feels rather unwieldy for reading and feels too overly-complicated from the standpoint of a bureaucratic group and for a person talking about it. For instance, it would be a mouthful for field agents if they have to use overtly long names.</p>
<p>But of course, it did use Able, Bravo etc. to make things shorter. And I understand your usage of the codenames to imply that each spear has its specific powers.</p>

							</div>

								
					
